Step 1: Open Azure DevOps

Open:

Azure DevOps

Login using Microsoft account.

Step 2: Create Project
Click New Project
Enter:
Project Name
Description
Select:
Private/Public
Click Create
Step 3: Prepare Maven/Gradle Project
Maven Structure
project/
 ├── pom.xml
 └── src/
Gradle Structure
project/
 ├── build.gradle
 └── src/
Step 4: Push Project to GitHub
git init

git checkout -b devops

git add .

git commit -m "Initial commit"

git remote add origin <repository-url>

git push -u origin devops
Step 5: Open Azure Repos

Go to:

Repos → Files

Observe repository files.

Step 6: Create Pipeline

Go to:

Pipelines → Create Pipeline
Step 7: Select Repository Source

Choose:

GitHub
OR
Azure Repos Git

Authorize access if needed.

Step 8: Select Repository

Select your repository and click:

Select
Step 9: Configure Pipeline

Choose:

Starter Pipeline

Azure DevOps automatically detects:

Maven project
OR
Gradle project
Step 10: Add YAML File
Maven YAML
trigger:
- main

pool:
  vmImage: ubuntu-latest

steps:
- task: Maven@4
  inputs:
    mavenPomFile: 'pom.xml'
    goals: 'clean package'
Step 11: Save Pipeline

Click:

Save and Run
Step 12: Execute Pipeline

Pipeline automatically:

Downloads source code
Builds project
Runs tests
Step 13: Monitor Logs

Observe:

Compilation logs
Dependency download
Build status
Step 14: Run Unit Tests

Example output:

Tests Run: 5
Failures: 0
BUILD SUCCESS
Step 15: Generate Reports

Generated reports:

Test reports
Build reports
Artifact details
Step 16: Verify Status
Pipeline Status: SUCCESS
